Name: Wormskin Folio: 1
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this living document. They read:

'The worm lord towers above the dusty earth; its flesh becomes the sky.
Our pathetic shells cannot follow, cannot reach its height, cannot reach its depths.
We offer ourselves to the ground.
We beg our sacrifice accepted.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 2
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this living document. They read:

'The dust was choking. 
Our eyes reddened and watered. 
But the truth was inescapable.
The veins of the Atlas had surfaced.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 3
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this living document. They read:

'Now with every storm we beg to be chosen;
Arms to the sky, faces to the dirt, calling out with all we have!
When heavy raindrops hit the earth, the veins of Atlas answer.
The rapture of our consumption is beyond words.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 4
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this living document. They read:

'We tumble as it swallows, but grip the slick walls as best we can - 
Oh! - to reach the gizzard still awake. 
Breathe it deeply! How our lungs gurgle!
The slime clogs our noses and stings our eyes, 
though in this warm darkness, we are already blind.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 5
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this living document. They read:

'Curse the agony of regurgitation, 
Curse this this feeble flesh that still confines me!
My brethren were reborn, rising from the blessed dust as fresh tendrils. 
Glistening capillaries to the great veins, slithering away into the sand.
I will be patient. Until the next storm.'

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 1 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a troubled freighter captain. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"We Blight this new galaxy, as we did the last, as we will the next!"

The data is of value to pirate faction The Blight, who attempted to retrieve it by violent means.

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 2 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a freighter shot down by pirate faction The Blight. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"The galactic tunnels belong to the Blight!"

The navigational information is corrupted, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the freighter captain.

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 3 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a starship crashed on an ocean bed. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"Annihilate every Traveller! All galaxies will fall to Blight!"

The navigational information is unreadable in its current state, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the freighter captain.

Name: Rendezvous Beacon
Description:

Use Activate Beacon (FE_ALT1) to deploy the beacon and retrace the final steps of the crashed ship.

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT I
Description:
A memory is burned into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The leviathan was like nothing I've ever seen.
So vast as to blot out the sun.
I wanted it. I deserve to have it! It will be mine.
But it resisted, would not come quietly.
It wailed and it wailed as the infra-knife carved into its meat.
It almost took me down with it. Perhaps it has. Perhaps..."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT II
Description:
A memory is burned into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The same nightmare chases me: a wail fills my cockpit, the dashboard controls gummed with blood.
I have given up sleep. I pulse past blurred stars.
And then there it was: majestic, drifting in the ocean of space.
Something inside me burns for it. I must have it.
Its great fin flexed toward my ship, and my hull was gone..."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT III
Description:
A memory is burned into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"Today should have been the day. Their hour was at hand.
It must be mine. They are like nothing I've ever seen.
Everything was prepared. But it moved faster than I thought possible. As though it knew where I would fly, before I knew it myself.
A great tentacle hugged my ship, my cockpit - pressing my suit down to the bone. This suit will be my grave."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT IV
Description:
A memory is burned into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The chase is over, and I have lost.
The giants will endure, and I will end.
As I plummeted from the sky, I saw another ship falling alongside mine. Then another, and another.
I may have imagined it. The misfiring of a dying mind...
Those creatures were so beautiful. But it is all ended now.
They will haunt my thoughts no longer."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT V
Description:
A memory is burned into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"I came face-to-face with a creature more beautiful and bizarre than anything I have ever seen.
Despite no discernible eyes, I do not believe it is blind.
It was huge, glorious, serene. But then - with a flick of its tentacles, it was gone.
I have thought of nothing else since. I can only think of the whale. whale. whale. wail."

Name: The Angler's Diary
Description:
A message recovered from a bottle stowed beneath the seat of the starship. It reads:

"I finally feel like I'm getting closer. A trader on Gisto offered me solid-gold information on its location, for a price.
And so I'm selling my ship. I'll miss the Celeste, but I have to know if the rumours are true. I hope whoever buys you takes good care of you..."

Description:

"The rumours were true. It's out there, I can feel it. Not here, but somewhere. The water calls to me, I just need to follow its voice..."
%PARTY_3%

Name: The Angler's Diary
Description:

"I saw it in my dreams last night. Scales like fire and eyes of pure starlight. It sang to me, a song of hope and longing. It wants me to find it, I know it. I must be closing in."
%PARTY_4%

Name: The Angler's Diary
Description:

"I was right! It was here! After all these light years, all the doubts, it's finally mine. Oh, and how it shines! Like fire in the water, beautiful, impossible..."
%PARTY_5%

Name: The Angler's Diary
Description:
A scrap of paper recovered from a bottle found bobbling in the water. The message on it reads:

"The fire has faded from my catch's scales, and my dreams have soured. I thrash through the night. My skin itches, damp and clammy. Salt seeps from my pores.
It longs to be free. I cannot keep it contained like this. It must be free.
I must be free..."

Name: The Angler
Description:
Fire dances across the scales of this impossible marine being. Its starlit eyes stare back at you with a meaning far deeper than any fish should know. As they stare, the world around you fades away.

The sound of water fills your ears. It wants to be free. You want to be free...

Description:
A flowing silken shroud, bestowed upon those who would sing with Voice of Freedom.

Name: Starborn Phoenix
Description:
An exclusive reforged starship, commemorating a time when Travellers old and new joined together to voyage across the stars.

This unusual ship is optimised for effortless gliding during flight, while a localised vector field allows the craft to hover above solid planes.

Claim this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU).

Name: Horizon Vector Nx
Description:
An exclusive Starship. This compact fighter craft boasts superior manoeuvrability, giving it an edge in space combat.

Claim this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU).

Name: Infinite Neon Mark Xxii
Description:
An exclusive Multi-Tool. This brightly-coloured rifle offers the user cutting-edge defensive capabilities in ground combat situations.

Take this Multi-Tool to add it to your collection, or Exchange it with your current Multi-Tool. Swap between active Multi-Tools from the Utilities section of the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU).

Name: Streamlined Jetpack Unit
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

A streamlined and lightweight backpack unit, featuring an elegant single-thruster design. This exclusive exosuit augmentation commemorates completion of the inaugural Expedition, 'Pioneers'.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Golden First Spawn Battle Mask
Description:
An aggressive Exosuit Appearance Override, modeled on the war helmets of the ancient Gek. This special edition is cast in a durable and precious alloy.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Golden Vector
Description:
An exclusive golden edition of the iconic Alpha Vector Starship, commemorating completion of the inaugural Expedition, 'Pioneers'.

This highly-manoeuvrable spacecraft is constructed from a durable and precious alloy, and coated in a tough layer of fibrous insulation to endure many lifetimes' worth of rigorous space exploration.

Claim this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU).

Name: Atlas Firework Pack
Description:
A three-variety pack of luxury fireworks. These stunning pyrotechnics render the likeness of an Atlas Interface, in bursts of indium, gold and cadmium. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky.

Place launch tube via the Build Menu (BUILD_MENU). Warning: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Flesh Launcher Pack
Description:
A pack of luxury fireworks. These organic pyrotechnics rocket into the sky and explode in a splatter of slime, mucus, and wormlets. Ignite to create disgusting displays in the sky.

Place launch tube via the Build Menu (BUILD_MENU). Warning: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Ssv Normandy Sr1
Description:
The SSV Normandy SR1 is a one-of-a-kind 'deep scout' frigate. This legendary ship represents peace and cooperation between races, and commemorates completion of the 'Beachhead' Expedition.

Recruiting this frigate will add it to your fleet. Manage your frigate fleet from a Fleet Command Room aboard your freighter, and consult your Navigator to deploy frigates on lucrative expeditions.

Name: Reality Glitch Trail

Description:

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

Description:
An exclusive Freighter Engine Flare Modifier.

The extreme heat of the freighter's engines excites this filter of sodium salts, tinting the exhaust with a vivid golden hue.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the Upgrade Control Terminal on the bridge.

Name: Antimatter Freighter Trail
Description:

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the Upgrade Control Terminal on the bridge.

Name: Hadal Freighter Trail
Description:

Organically altering the hue of freighter exhaust, this engine modification utilises the bioluminescence of abyssal sea creatures to generate its striking turquoise colouration.

Transform the appearance of your freighter at the Upgrade Control Terminal on the bridge.

Name: Tentacled Cape
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

Flow across the galaxy with this cape's lattice of fluttering tentacles, woven from regenerated cellulose fibres.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Cosmic Megafauna Cape
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

In the furthest reaches of space swim cosmic megafauna, aligning their paths with Travellers, dreaming of possible realities.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Titan Worm Cape
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

"The worm lord towers above the dusty earth; its flesh becomes the sky."

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Description:

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Spawning Cowl
Description:
This grand hood is worn by the upper ranks of Gek at events and conventions, distinguishing the esteemed Trade Lord from the lowly Hireling.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit with this exclusive Appearance Override at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Scorching Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

Pressurised jets breathe additional oxygen into the Jetpack flames, brightening and lengthening the exhaust trail.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Festive Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

A multi-coloured scattering of bio-plastic flakes adds a celebratory flair to the Jetpack's output. Expelled material is fully compostable.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Pyrotechnic Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

Pellets of chromatic metal ignite during flight, splitting into glittering stars of RGB.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Plasma Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

Replaces the standard Jetpack combustion chamber with a plasma engine. During flight, the exhaust nozzles release dazzling clouds of ionised matter.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Fusion Jetpack Trail
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.

Harnesses natural stellar processes to make the Jetpack output blaze. A light-diffusing compound protects the user and onlookers from retinal damage.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Rebuilt Exosuit Module
Description:
A salvaged upgrade for the Exosuit. Use FE_ALT1 to begin upgrade installation process.

Constructed by the Autophage, this technology package is the result of a high degree of engineering improvisation. As a one-of-a-kind piece of repurposed technology, its exact effect upon suit performance is hard to determine prior to installation within the Exosuit's systems.

Name: Singing Sea-snail
Description: "A voice like honey from a mouth of mucus."

Name: Golden Jellyfish
Description: "Its tentacles that glitter like wisps of golden hair, but sting with the fire of thousand suns."

Name: Dragonfish
Description: "Territorial, ancient, furious to be caught. The king of the sea."

Name: The Lunker
Description: "A true titan of the depths. Nothing compares for sheer mass."

Name: Emeril Sunstar
Description: "Its perfect crystalline form glistens with a emerald light that changes the soul of all those whose eyes fall upon it."

Name: Vampire Squid
Description: "A true error of the deep; its hungry bite corrupts your blood, filling your body with a spurting corrosive bile."

Name: Bleached Bonefish
Description: "Robbed of flesh and stripped of colour by acid seas, the bonefish swims on regardless."

Name: Translucent Gulper
Description: "Seemingly weak and fragile at the surface, these giant jaws have swallowed alive many an unwary soul who ventured into their abyssal home..."

Name: Many-eyed Jellyfish
Description: "A thousand eyes erupt from its soft flesh: a never-ending cycle of rising, blinking, sinking, and re-emergence."

Name: Aberrant Duskfin
Description: "Its wings beat slowly as it sails though the poisoned seas, a drifter with no place of rest, no end to their journey."

Name: Gamma Squid
Description: "A pale blue glow surrounds it as it drifts through the water - a warning to all those who would come too close..."

Name: Helix Sawfish
Description: "Polymorphic, twisting, always in motion; its body a constant whirr of shifting forms and ripping teeth."

Name: Starshell Crab
Description: "Its glittering shell is practically unbreakable, a material of pure perfection."

Name: Mirrorscale Skipper
Description: "Impossible to see with mortal eyes as it flashes through the water under boiling, cloudless skies."

Name: Jelly of the Veil
Description: "A dark cloud follows this creature, and dreams of doom await all those who touch it."

Name: Ancient Irontail
Description: "Heart of stone and fins of iron, this creature lives on where all else falters."

Name: Crystal Jelly
Description: "A living snowflake: frozen solid yet still alive, its tentacles a fractal recursion."

Name: Ghostfin
Description: "A name only spoken in whispers, its pale body a illusion that flickers beneath the moonlit waves."

Name: Iceblood Gulper
Description: "A heart that beats but once a hour, a heart that sees faster life spawn and die, spawn and die, spawn and die..."

Name: Nautilia
Description: "None would believe the scale of this beast: its colossal shell, its enormous slimy foot. None, except those who have seen it..."

Name: Glass Angel
Description: "A creature of dreams, only visible where the light refracts through its soft, perfect jelly."

Name: Mist Serpent
Description: "When hunting, can dissolve into a thin dark cloud, impossible to track, impossible to see coming..."

Name: Reef Guardian
Description: "A powerful, muscular body and teeth like razors, these gentle giants protect smaller creatures from predators."

Name: Blind Titancore
Description: "The old man of the sea; scarred, blinded, still swimming on..."

Name: Fragile Icthyoscale
Description: "A delicate creature, a fragment of the past that lives on in the water."

Name: Titanworm Larva
Description: "The many-mouths arise from the darkness of the ocean; the many-mouths hunger for their home in the sand..."

Name: Ossified Deinosuchus
Description: "A relic of another age, a fusion of life and stone that refuses to die."

Name: Megalodon
Description: "The apex of marine predation, a perfect killing machine. Beware."

Name: Sentient Crab
Description: "Deep feeling swims in those watery eyestalks, the thoughtful intelligence of a true ancient."

Name: Brain Eel
Description: "It slides beneath the waves; it slides between the ears; it slides within the folds, and swims forever in your dreams."

Name: The Hunter Below
Description: "Streamlined, deadly, perfect: the terror of the deep."

Name: Leviathan Spawn
Description: "So young and fragile, despite its years beneath the waves. And yet thousands more years must pass before it joins the great herd in the stars..."

Name: Mandelbrot Worm
Description: "The geometry of its impossible body folds within itself, a writhing thread of flesh and spacetime."

Name: Mother-of-quicksilver
Description: "Brilliantly ablaze, its surface a perfect liquid sun..."

Name: Hyper-cockle
Description: "Both alive and not alive; at once a creature, a mineral, and a moment from another time..."

Name: The Maw of Titan
Description: "So few things survive in waters such as these... so that which thrives should strike fear into the heart of any thinking being."

Name: Abyssal Horror Egg
Description: "Listen to these words: Do not allow this egg to hatch. Cast it back into the sea."

Name: Atlantidian Crab
Description: "Shell and claw of perfect crystal, eyestalks aglow with purple rage; a being displaced from another reality and cast here as crab."

Name: Child of Helios
Description: "Its song resonates across time and space, calling to its home in the endless black above. One day, it will rise and return to its home among the stars."

Name: Many-mouthed Lunker
Description: "On the surface or below the waves, the vessel hungers, the vessel feeds..."

Description:

Description:

This limb override also functions as its own dedicated combat system. It deploys high-velocity stun projectiles and serves as an excellent support weapon to the Minotaur's primary cannon.
